Insecure Direct Object Reference (IDOR): The most common "low-hanging" but high-impact bug. Simply change a resource ID in a URL or request (e.g., changing user_id=123 to user_id=124) to see if you can access another user's data.
Information Leakage: Scrutinize publicly accessible files like robots.txt, .git/ directories, .env files, or configuration backups (e.g., config.php.bak).
Broken Authentication & Session Management:
  Test if a session remains active after a password change in a different browser.
  Check for password reset token reuse (using the same link twice to change a password).
  Verify if administrative panels are accessible with default credentials like admin:admin.
Misconfigured Cloud Storage: Search for open Amazon S3 buckets or unprotected Firebase databases using tools like Shodan.
Simple XSS & Open Redirects: Test input fields and URL parameters for reflected Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) or redirections to malicious external sites. 
 
